      "message": "The \"settled\" formula on the overview card fires on the very first watcher invocation (with `immediate: true`), before any data is fetched.\n\nSuggested fix — gate on the chassis collection actually being fetched and either the metrics being fetched or the URI being unavailable:\n```\nconst { data: chassisMembers, isFetched: chassisFetched } \u003d useRedfishCollection\u003cChassis\u003e(...);\n// ...\nconst settled \u003d computed(() \u003d\u003e {\n  if (!chassisFetched.value) return false;\n  if (!environmentMetricsUri.value) return true; // no chassis with EnvironmentMetrics\n  return metricsQuery.isFetched.value \u0026\u0026 !metricsQuery.isFetching.value;\n});\n```\nThen watch settled directly. (You\u0027ll need useRedfishCollection to expose isFetched, or expose it through usePowerControl.)",
